 {"id":"bd-3al","title":"Implement client-side task management methods","description":"# Client-Side Task Management Methods

## Background
Python FastMCP client supports task management methods for interacting with server task queues. The server-side Docket is implemented, but client methods are missing.

## Requirements

### Client Task Methods
```rust
impl Client {
    /// Submit a background task
    pub async fn submit_task(
        &self,
        cx: Cx,
        task_type: &str,
        input: Value,
    ) -> McpResult<TaskSubmitResult>

    /// List tasks with optional status filter
    pub async fn list_tasks(
        &self,
        cx: Cx,
        status: Option<TaskStatus>,
        cursor: Option<&str>,
    ) -> McpResult<ListTasksResult>

    /// Get task details
    pub async fn get_task(
        &self,
        cx: Cx,
        task_id: &str,
    ) -> McpResult<TaskInfo>

    /// Cancel a running task
    pub async fn cancel_task(
        &self,
        cx: Cx,
        task_id: &str,
        reason: Option<&str>,
    ) -> McpResult<()>

    /// Wait for task completion with polling
    pub async fn wait_for_task(
        &self,
        cx: Cx,
        task_id: &str,
        poll_interval: Duration,
    ) -> McpResult<TaskResult>
}
```

### Protocol Types (fastmcp-protocol)
Ensure these exist:
```rust
pub struct TaskSubmitParams { task_type: String, input: Value }
pub struct TaskSubmitResult { task_id: String }
pub struct ListTasksParams { status: Option<TaskStatus>, cursor: Option<String> }
pub struct ListTasksResult { tasks: Vec<TaskInfo>, next_cursor: Option<String> }
pub struct TaskInfo { id: String, status: TaskStatus, ... }
pub struct TaskResult { output: Value, ... }
```

### JSON-RPC Methods
- tasks/submit → TaskSubmitResult
- tasks/list → ListTasksResult
- tasks/get → TaskInfo
- tasks/cancel → empty result

## Testing
- Test submit_task sends correct JSON-RPC
- Test list_tasks with/without filter
- Test get_task retrieves details
- Test cancel_task sends cancellation
- Test wait_for_task polls correctly

## Files to Modify
- crates/fastmcp-protocol/src/types.rs (ensure task types)
- crates/fastmcp-client/src/lib.rs

